               <persName>
                  <roleName type="title">ʾazzāž</roleName>
               </persName>
                  <occupation type="military">leader</occupation>
                  
               <floruit notBefore="1574" notAfter="1596">He was a trusted 
                  <persName ref="PRS5014Halibo">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾazzāž</roleName>
                     Halibo</persName> at the court of <persName ref="PRS8550sardaDe">
                        <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                     </persName>. As such he was appointed commander of 
                  a newly organized guard regiment <persName ref="PRS11801Qurban">qʷǝrbān</persName> 
                  in <date>1574</date>
                  and served loyally his sovereign both as warlord and diplomat.  
                  A year later, in <date>1575</date>, he was sent as a head of delegation of high ecclesiastics to 
                  <persName ref="PRS10343Yeshaq">
                     <roleName type="title">bahǝr nagāš </roleName>
                  </persName>
                   to pledge loyality to the emperor. 
                  He is also known to have taken part with his regiment in a successful campaign of the Emperor against the 
                  <persName ref="ETH1274Betaes"/> prince <persName ref="PRS5842Kalef"/> in October <date>1597</date>.
               </floruit>   
                 
